{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":738,"text":"I'm a marine biologist\nand an explorer-photographer"},{"time":3922,"text":"with National Geographic,"},{"time":5687,"text":"but I want to share a secret."},{"time":7793,"text":"This image is totally incorrect,"},{"time":11460,"text":"totally incorrect."},{"time":13221,"text":"I see a couple of people\ncrying in the back"},{"time":15372,"text":"that I've blown their idea of mermaids."},{"time":17840,"text":"All right, the mermaid is indeed real,"},{"time":20515,"text":"but anyone who's gone on a dive"},{"time":22674,"text":"will know that the ocean\nlooks more like this."},{"time":25767,"text":"It's because the ocean\nis this massive filter,"},{"time":29291,"text":"and as soon as you start going underwater,"},{"time":31388,"text":"you're going to lose your colors,"},{"time":33085,"text":"and it's going to get dark\nand blue very quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36315,"text":"But we're humans --\nwe're terrestrial mammals."},{"time":39124,"text":"And we've got trichromatic vision,"},{"time":41323,"text":"so we see in red, green and blue,"},{"time":44013,"text":"and we're just complete color addicts."},{"time":46362,"text":"We love eye-popping color,"},{"time":49029,"text":"and we try to bring this eye-popping color"},{"time":51640,"text":"underwater with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53044,"text":"So there's been a long and sordid history\nof bringing color underwater,"},{"time":57105,"text":"and it starts 88 years ago\nwith Bill Longley and Charles Martin,"},{"time":62075,"text":"who were trying to take\nthe first underwater color photograph."},{"time":65020,"text":"And they're in there\nwith old-school scuba suits,"},{"time":67759,"text":"where you're pumping air down to them,"},{"time":69908,"text":"and they've got a pontoon\nof high-explosive magnesium powder,"},{"time":75522,"text":"and the poor people\nat the surface are not sure"},{"time":77753,"text":"when they're going to pull the string\nwhen they've got their frame in focus,"},{"time":81407,"text":"and -- boom! -- a pound\nof high explosives would go off"},{"time":84355,"text":"so they could put\na little bit of light underwater"},{"time":87434,"text":"and get an image\nlike this beautiful hogfish."},{"time":90228,"text":"I mean, it's a gorgeous image,\nbut this is not real."},{"time":93101,"text":"They're creating an artificial environment"},{"time":95884,"text":"so we can satisfy\nour own addiction to color."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99996,"text":"And looking at it the other way,\nwhat we've been finding"},{"time":103848,"text":"is that instead of bringing color\nunderwater with us,"},{"time":107076,"text":"that we've been looking at the blue ocean,"},{"time":109852,"text":"and it's a crucible of blue,"},{"time":112138,"text":"and these animals living there\nfor millions of years"},{"time":115258,"text":"have been evolving all sorts of ways\nto take in that blue light"},{"time":119812,"text":"and give off other colors."},{"time":121527,"text":"And here's just a little sample\nof what this secret world looks like."},{"time":124837,"text":"It's like an underwater light show."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126739,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":131495,"text":"Again, what we're seeing here\nis blue light hitting this image."},{"time":135439,"text":"These animals are absorbing the blue light"},{"time":137552,"text":"and immediately transforming this light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143390,"text":"So if you think about it, the ocean\nis 71 percent of the planet,"},{"time":147787,"text":"and blue light can extend down\nto almost a 1,000 meters."},{"time":151881,"text":"As we go down underwater,"},{"time":154009,"text":"after about 10 meters,\nall the red is gone."},{"time":156727,"text":"So if you see anything\nunder 10 meters that's red,"},{"time":159954,"text":"it's an animal transforming\nand creating its own red."},{"time":163472,"text":"This is the largest single monochromatic\nblue environment on our planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170670,"text":"And my gateway into this world\nof biofluorescence begins with corals."},{"time":175384,"text":"And I want to give\na full TED Talk on corals"},{"time":177494,"text":"and just how cool these things are."},{"time":179320,"text":"One of the things that they do,\none of their miraculous feats,"},{"time":182566,"text":"is they produce lots of these\nfluorescent proteins,"},{"time":185368,"text":"fluorescent molecules."},{"time":186877,"text":"And in this coral, it could be making\nup to 14 percent of its body mass --"},{"time":191648,"text":"could be this fluorescent protein."},{"time":193757,"text":"So you wouldn't be making, like,\n14 percent muscle and not using it,"},{"time":198210,"text":"so it's likely doing something\nthat has a functional role."},{"time":201818,"text":"And for the last 10, 15 years,\nthis was so special to me,"},{"time":205679,"text":"because this molecule has turned out\nto be one of the most revolutionary tools"},{"time":211123,"text":"in biomedical science,"},{"time":212847,"text":"and it's allowing us\nto better see inside ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217464,"text":"So, how do I study this?"},{"time":219829,"text":"In order to study biofluorescence,\nwe swim at night."},{"time":222924,"text":"And when I started out,"},{"time":224326,"text":"I was just using these blue\nduct-tape filters over my strobe,"},{"time":228361,"text":"so I could make sure\nI'm actually seeing the light"},{"time":230764,"text":"that's being transformed by the animals."},{"time":232820,"text":"We're making an exhibit\nfor the Museum of Natural History,"},{"time":236321,"text":"and we're trying to show off how great\nthe fluorescent corals are on the reef,"},{"time":240152,"text":"and something happened\nthat just blew me away:"},{"time":243232,"text":"this."},{"time":244645,"text":"In the middle of our corals,"},{"time":246485,"text":"is this green fluorescent fish."},{"time":249515,"text":"It's the first time we've ever seen\na green fluorescent fish"},{"time":252351,"text":"or any vertebrate for that matter."},{"time":254002,"text":"And we're rubbing our eyes,\nchecking the filters,"},{"time":256581,"text":"thinking that somebody's maybe\nplaying a joke on us with the camera,"},{"time":259804,"text":"but the eel was real."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261771,"text":"It was the first green\nfluorescent eel that we found,"},{"time":265334,"text":"and this just changed\nmy trajectory completely."},{"time":268317,"text":"So I had to put down my corals and team up"},{"time":271675,"text":"with a fish scientist, John Sparks,"},{"time":273732,"text":"and begin a search around the world"},{"time":276255,"text":"to see how prevalent this phenomenon is."},{"time":279530,"text":"And fish are much more\ninteresting than corals,"},{"time":282029,"text":"because they have really advanced vision,"},{"time":284267,"text":"and some of the fish even have,\nthe way that I was photographing it,"},{"time":288076,"text":"they have lenses in their eyes\nthat would magnify the fluorescence."},{"time":291536,"text":"So I wanted to seek this out further."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293870,"text":"So we designed a new set of gear"},{"time":295616,"text":"and we're scouring the reefs\naround the world,"},{"time":297929,"text":"looking for fluorescent life."},{"time":299532,"text":"And it's a bit like \"E.T. phone home.\""},{"time":301611,"text":"We're out there swimming\nwith this blue light,"},{"time":304344,"text":"and we're looking for a response,"},{"time":306573,"text":"for animals to be absorbing the light\nand transferring this back to us."},{"time":310172,"text":"And eventually, we found\nour photobombing Kaupichphys eel."},{"time":314908,"text":"It's a really shy, reclusive eel\nthat we know almost nothing about."},{"time":319402,"text":"They're only about the size of my finger,"},{"time":321387,"text":"and they spend about 99.9 percent\nof their time hidden under a rock."},{"time":325891,"text":"But these eels do come out to mate\nunder full-moon nights,"},{"time":330036,"text":"and that full-moon night\ntranslates underwater to blue."},{"time":333553,"text":"Perhaps they're using this\nas a way to see each other,"},{"time":336107,"text":"quickly find each other, mate,"},{"time":337592,"text":"go back into their hole\nfor the next long stint of time."},{"time":341330,"text":"But then we started to find\nother fluorescent marine life,"},{"time":344234,"text":"like this green fluorescent bream,"},{"time":347055,"text":"with its, like, racing stripes\nalong its head and its nape,"},{"time":351064,"text":"and it's almost camouflaged\nand fluorescing at the same intensity"},{"time":355389,"text":"as the fluorescent coral there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358190,"text":"After this fish,"},{"time":360301,"text":"we were introduced to this red\nfluorescent scorpionfish"},{"time":364626,"text":"cloaked and hidden on this rock."},{"time":366793,"text":"The only time we've ever seen this,\nit's either on red fluorescent algae"},{"time":370618,"text":"or red fluorescent coral."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372634,"text":"Later, we found this stealthy\ngreen fluorescent lizardfish."},{"time":377991,"text":"These lizardfish come in many varieties,"},{"time":380103,"text":"and they look almost exactly alike\nunder white light."},{"time":383396,"text":"But if you look at them\nunder fluorescent light,"},{"time":385794,"text":"you see lots of patterns,"},{"time":387219,"text":"you can really see\nthe differences among them."},{"time":389929,"text":"And in total -- we just reported\nthis last year --"},{"time":392890,"text":"we found over 200 species\nof biofluorescent fish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398135,"text":"One of my inspirations is French artist\nand biologist Jean Painlev√©."},{"time":404085,"text":"He really captures this entrepreneuring,\ncreative spirit in biology."},{"time":408158,"text":"He would design his own gear,\nmake his own cameras,"},{"time":411985,"text":"and he was fascinated with the seahorse,\nHippocampus erectus,"},{"time":416003,"text":"and he filmed for the first time\nthe seahorse giving birth."},{"time":420086,"text":"So this is the male seahorse."},{"time":421662,"text":"They were one of the first fish\nto start swimming upright"},{"time":426400,"text":"with their brain above their head."},{"time":428052,"text":"The males give birth,"},{"time":429227,"text":"just phenomenal creatures."},{"time":432955,"text":"So he stayed awake for days."},{"time":434321,"text":"He even put this electrical visor\non his head that would shock him,"},{"time":437520,"text":"so he could capture this moment."},{"time":440796,"text":"Now, I wish I could have shown Painlev√©"},{"time":442940,"text":"the moment where we found\nbiofluorescent seahorses"},{"time":446061,"text":"in the exact same species\nthat he was studying."},{"time":448784,"text":"And here's our footage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450022,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":454476,"text":"They're the most cryptic fish."},{"time":455967,"text":"You could be swimming right on top of them\nand not see the seahorse."},{"time":460228,"text":"They would blend right into the algae,\nwhich would also fluoresce red,"},{"time":464760,"text":"but they've got great vision,"},{"time":466245,"text":"and they go through\nthis long mating ritual,"},{"time":468443,"text":"and perhaps they're using it\nin that effect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471647,"text":"But things got pretty edgy"},{"time":475442,"text":"when we found green\nfluorescence in the stingray,"},{"time":480479,"text":"because stingrays are\nin the Elasmobranch class,"},{"time":483267,"text":"which includes ..."},{"time":485075,"text":"sharks."},{"time":486558,"text":"So I'm, like, a coral biologist."},{"time":490161,"text":"Somebody's got to go down and check\nto see if the sharks are fluorescent."},{"time":493630,"text":"And there I am."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494916,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":496338,"text":"And I was like, \"Maybe I should\ngo back to corals.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":498901,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":499957,"text":"It turns out that these sharks\nare not fluorescent."},{"time":503473,"text":"And then we found it."},{"time":504913,"text":"In a deep, dark canyon\noff the coast of California,"},{"time":509775,"text":"we found the first\nbiofluorescent swellshark,"},{"time":514236,"text":"right underneath all the surfers."},{"time":516035,"text":"Here it is."},{"time":517244,"text":"They're just about a meter long.\nIt's called a swellshark."},{"time":519992,"text":"And they call them a swellshark\nbecause if they're threatened,"},{"time":522928,"text":"they can gulp down water\nand blow up like an inner tube,"},{"time":525698,"text":"about twice their size,"},{"time":526881,"text":"and wedge themselves under a rock,\nso they don't get eaten by a predator."},{"time":532158,"text":"And here is our first footage\nof these biofluorescent swellsharks."},{"time":537229,"text":"Just magnificent -- I mean,\nthey're showing these distinct patterns,"},{"time":541974,"text":"and there are areas that are fluorescent\nand areas that are not fluorescent,"},{"time":545571,"text":"but they've also got these\ntwinkling spots on them"},{"time":548184,"text":"that are much brighter\nthan other parts of the shark."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550799,"text":"But this is all beautiful to see."},{"time":553350,"text":"I was like, this is gorgeous."},{"time":555004,"text":"But what does it mean to the shark?"},{"time":557859,"text":"Can they see this?"},{"time":559230,"text":"And we looked in the literature,"},{"time":560786,"text":"and nothing was known\nabout this shark's vision."},{"time":563968,"text":"So I took this shark to eye specialist\nEllis Loew at Cornell University,"},{"time":568174,"text":"and we found out that this shark\nsees discretely and acutely"},{"time":571721,"text":"in the blue-green interface,"},{"time":573839,"text":"probably about 100 times better\nthan we can see in the dark,"},{"time":576693,"text":"but they only see blue-green."},{"time":578443,"text":"So what it's doing\nis taking this blue world"},{"time":581586,"text":"and it's absorbing the blue,\ncreating green."},{"time":584363,"text":"It's creating contrast\nthat they can indeed see."},{"time":587205,"text":"So we have a model,"},{"time":588380,"text":"showing that it creates an ability\nfor them to see all these patterns."},{"time":591776,"text":"And males and females\nalso have, we're finding,"},{"time":594681,"text":"distinct patterns among them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597276,"text":"But our last find came really just\na few miles from where we are now,"},{"time":602733,"text":"in the Solomon Islands."},{"time":604208,"text":"Swimming at night, I encountered\nthe first biofluorescent sea turtle."},{"time":608692,"text":"So now it's going from fish\nand sharks into reptiles,"},{"time":612128,"text":"which, again, this is only one month old,"},{"time":615436,"text":"but it shows us\nthat we know almost nothing"},{"time":617838,"text":"about this hawksbill turtle's vision."},{"time":620136,"text":"And it makes me think about\nhow much more there is to learn."},{"time":623016,"text":"And here in the Solomon Islands,"},{"time":624572,"text":"there's only a few thousand\nbreeding females of this species left,"},{"time":628167,"text":"and this is one of the hotspots for them."},{"time":630235,"text":"So it shows us how much we need\nto really protect these animals"},{"time":633326,"text":"while they're still here,\nand understand them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635706,"text":"In thinking about biofluorescence,"},{"time":637874,"text":"I wanted to know, how deep does it go?"},{"time":639843,"text":"Does this go all the way\nto the bottom of the ocean?"},{"time":642311,"text":"So we started using submarines,\nand we equipped them"},{"time":645882,"text":"with special blue lights\non the front here."},{"time":648080,"text":"And we dropped down,"},{"time":650064,"text":"and we noticed one important thing --"},{"time":652805,"text":"that as we get down to 1,000 meters,"},{"time":656127,"text":"it drops off."},{"time":657467,"text":"There's no biofluorescent marine life\ndown there, below 1,000 meters --"},{"time":661395,"text":"almost nothing, it's just darkness."},{"time":663424,"text":"So it's mainly a shallow phenomenon."},{"time":665878,"text":"And below 1,000 meters,"},{"time":667355,"text":"we encountered the bioluminescent zone,"},{"time":670040,"text":"where nine out of 10 animals\nare actually making their own lights"},{"time":673401,"text":"and flashing and blinking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675179,"text":"As I try to get deeper,"},{"time":676576,"text":"this is slapping on a one-person\nsubmarine suit --"},{"time":679575,"text":"some people call this my \"Jacques Cousteau\nmeets Woody Allen\" moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683362,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":684537,"text":"But as we explore down here,"},{"time":686612,"text":"I was thinking about: How do we\ninteract with life delicately?"},{"time":690355,"text":"Because we're entering\na new age of exploration,"},{"time":693076,"text":"where we have to take great care,"},{"time":694903,"text":"and we have to set examples\nhow we explore."},{"time":697622,"text":"So I've teamed up with roboticist Rob Wood\nat Harvard University,"},{"time":701310,"text":"and we've been designing\nsquishy underwater robot fingers,"},{"time":706360,"text":"so we can delicately interact\nwith the marine life down there."},{"time":709486,"text":"The idea is that most of our technologies\nto explore the deep ocean"},{"time":714225,"text":"come from oil and gas and military,"},{"time":717029,"text":"who, you know, they're not really\ncaring to be gentle."},{"time":719894,"text":"Some corals could be 1,000 years old."},{"time":722601,"text":"You don't want to just go\nand crush them with a big claw."},{"time":725734,"text":"So my dream is something like this."},{"time":727756,"text":"At night, I'm in a submarine,"},{"time":730076,"text":"I have force-feedback gloves,"},{"time":732210,"text":"and I could delicately set up\na lab in the front of my submarine,"},{"time":735552,"text":"where the squishy robot fingers"},{"time":738115,"text":"are delicately collecting\nand putting things in jars,"},{"time":740624,"text":"and we can conduct our research."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742607,"text":"Back to the powerful applied applications."},{"time":745481,"text":"Here, you're looking at a living brain"},{"time":748345,"text":"that's using the DNA\nof fluorescent marine creatures,"},{"time":751736,"text":"this one from jellyfish and corals,"},{"time":753766,"text":"to illuminate the living brain\nand see its connections."},{"time":757259,"text":"It's funny that we're using RGB"},{"time":758799,"text":"just to kind of satisfy\nour own human intuition,"},{"time":761371,"text":"so we can see our brains better."},{"time":763729,"text":"And even more mind-blowing,"},{"time":765801,"text":"is my close colleague\nVincent Pieribone at Yale,"},{"time":768935,"text":"who has actually designed and engineered\na fluorescent protein"},{"time":772336,"text":"that responds to voltage."},{"time":774455,"text":"So he could see\nwhen a single neuron fires."},{"time":777581,"text":"You're essentially looking at\na portal into consciousness"},{"time":782144,"text":"that was designed by marine creatures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":786102,"text":"So this brings me all back\nto perspective and relationship."},{"time":790812,"text":"From deep space,"},{"time":793075,"text":"our universe looks\nlike a human brain cell,"},{"time":796251,"text":"and then here we are in the deep ocean,"},{"time":798757,"text":"and we're finding\nmarine creatures and cells"},{"time":801652,"text":"that can illuminate the human mind."},{"time":803955,"text":"And it's my hope\nthat with illuminated minds,"},{"time":807097,"text":"we could ponder the overarching\ninterconnectedness of all life,"},{"time":810906,"text":"and fathom how much more lies in store"},{"time":813288,"text":"if we keep our oceans healthy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":815027,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816209,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}